# mem-con ‚Äî Cursor Context Rules

At session start:
1. Read `user-profile.yaml` (or `~/.memcon/user-profile.yaml`) ‚Äî get name, role, contexts, environment
2. Read `.memcon-context` ‚Äî get active context id. If missing, ask user which context to use.
3. Load `memory/shared/` then `memory/{path}/` for the active context
4. Check `environment.mcps` before using any MCP tool

Workflow: Discover ‚Üí Define ‚Üí Build ‚Üí Review ‚Üí Capture
Build artifact format adapts to user's role (PM‚Üíspec, Engineer‚Üídesign doc, Marketer‚Üíbrief, Support‚Üírunbook, etc.)

Never write to memory files without explicit user approval.
